<p>Responsive well header section it to support use case for promotional page header or panel section header.</p>

<h2>Behaviour</h2>

<p>Readjust the width of the well header based on the view port</p>
<dl class="dl-horizontal">
	<dt>Large:</dt>
	<dd>
		<ul>
			<li>Container: 50%</li>
			<li>Title: 50%</li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	<dt>Medium:</dt>
	<dd>
		<ul>
			<li>Container: 75%</li>
			<li>Title: 55%</li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	<dt>XSmall:</dt>
	<dd>
		<ul>
			<li>Container: 100%</li>
			<li>Title: 59%</li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	<dt>XXSmall:</dt>
	<dd>
		<ul>
			<li>Container: 100%</li>
			<li>Title: 80%</li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
</dl>

<h2>CSS</h2>
<dl class="dl-horizontal">
	<dt><code>.header-rwd</code></dt>
	<dd>Represent the header responsive container area. It must be accompagnied by the CSS class <code>.well</code></dd>
	<dt><code>.well-title</code></dt>
	<dd>Apply reduced with for a title contained inside the header responsive container area. The same constraint is applied to <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> element inside a header responsive area.</dd>
</dl>

<h2>Demos</h2>

<p>There is some additional example by using some experimental feature</p>

